Jenna Etheridge, News24Cape Town &ndash; Two motorbike riders died in a head-on collision in the Free State on Saturday afternoon, paramedics said.The accident between the pair, believed to be in their 40&rsquo;s, took place 20km outside Bloemfontein, said ER24 spokesperson Annine Dormehl.When paramedics arrived at 14:00, they found both bikes burning.The road had to be closed so the scene could be cleared, she said.Police were on the scene for further investigation. The accident scene outside Bloemfontein. (ER24)24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.